<body>
    <h1>COURSE OUTLINE</h1>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>INTRODUCTION</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Brief overview of the course.</li>
            <li>Importance of professional emails in business communication.</li>
            <li>What the students will learn: combining HTML for design and Python for automation.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>HTML BASICS</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Introduction to HTML: tags, elements, and attributes.</li>
            <li>Creating a basic email template with HTML.</li>
            <li>Styling with inline CSS (since many email clients strip out external CSS).</li>
            <li>Ensuring responsiveness and compatibility across different email clients.</li>
            <li>Adding elements like images, tables, and links.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>BUILDING THE EMAIL TEMPLATE</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Hands-on example: creating a simple yet professional email template.</li>
            <li>Emphasizing best practices (e.g., using tables for layout, inline styles, alt text for images).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>INTRODUCTION TO PYTHON FOR EMAIL AUTOMATION</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Setting up the environment: Installing Python, setting up a virtual environment.</li>
            <li>Overview of Python libraries used for email: smtplib, email, jinja2.</li>
            <li>Configuring SMTP (Simple Mail Transfer Protocol) for sending emails.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>INTEGRATING HTML WITH PYTHON</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Using jinja2 to create dynamic email templates.</li>
            <li>Sending an email using Python with the HTML template.</li>
            <li>Example: Sending a personalized email to multiple recipients.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>ADVANCED TECHNIQUES</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Adding attachments to emails.</li>
            <li>Handling errors and exceptions in email sending.</li>
            <li>Tracking email opens and clicks (using external services like Google Analytics or built-in tracking pixels).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>FINAL PROJECT</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Students create and send their own professional email using the skills learned.</li>
            <li>Review and feedback on their projects.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Q&A AND WRAP-UP</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Addressing any questions or challenges faced by students.</li>
            <li>Providing additional resources for further learning.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
